ary";s:297:"			<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/bookchiq/">bookchiq</a> posted a photo:</p>\n	\n<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/bookchiq/5908977007/" title="IMG_4922"><img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5277/5908977007_280bfdef20_m.jpg" width="179" height="240" alt="IMG_4922" /></a></p>\n\n";}i:14;a:9:{s:5:"title";s:36:"Raycom InfoTech Park Retail Addition";s:4:"link";s:53:"http://www.flickr.com/photos/61641763@N07/5908897121/";s:11:"description";s:1221:"			<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/61641763@N07/">MulvannyG2</a> posted a photo:</p>\n	\n<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/61641763@N07/5908897121/" title="Raycom InfoTech Park Retail Addition"><img src="http://farm7.static.flickr.com/6052/5908897121_a1acc71a51_m.jpg" width="240" height="156" alt="Raycom InfoTech Park Retail Addition" /></a></p>\n\n<p>Beijing, China – Raycom InfoTech Park is the first multifunctional business park for world-class enterprises in Zhongguancun, a technology hub in Beijing. MulvannyG2 was commissioned to create a new retail center within this hi-tech district to enhance the existing campus and more importantly create a fresh, up-scale gathering space to attract the growing intellectual elite in China. A simple, elegant channel-shaped frosted glass box acts as a beacon signaling visitors both day and night to the retail center’s entrance. Natural day lighting enhances the lifestyle gallery within filled with hip cuisine and dynamic storefronts. Connected to the business park by gardens and meandering paths the Raycom Retail Addition will completely transform the development into the new go-to location for shopping, dining, and people watching in Beijing.</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 06 Jul 2011 10:11:43 -0700";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:10:"date.taken";s:25:"2011-03-14T15:18:39-08:00";}s:6:"author";s:30:"nobody@flickr.com (MulvannyG2)";s:4:"guid";s:37:"tag:flickr.com,2004:/photo/5908897121";s:5:"media";a:4:{s:5:"title";s:36:"Raycom InfoTech Park Retail Additio